# AirWatch - Local Pollution Reporting App

Complete pollution reporting system with user submission, admin verification, community support, and real-time tracking.

---

## 📋 FEATURES (Per PDF Specification)

### User Features
✅ Registration & Login  
✅ Submit Pollution Reports (with photo, type, severity, location, GPS)  
✅ View Live Feed of approved reports  
✅ Filter & Search reports (by type, severity, location, date, keyword)  
✅ Track Report Status (Pending → Under Investigation → Action Taken → Resolved)  
✅ Community Support/Upvote System  
✅ Real-time Pollution Alerts (High severity)  
✅ Map Visualization (Leaflet.js)  
✅ AQI Widget (Air Quality Index)  
✅ Forum/Community Discussion  
✅ Notifications System  

### Admin Features
✅ Admin Dashboard with Statistics  
✅ Review & Validate Reports (checklist system)  
✅ Approve/Reject Reports  
✅ Update Report Status & Add Notes  
✅ View Admin Activity Logs  
✅ Reports & Analytics  
✅ Export to CSV  
✅ User Management  

---

## 🚀 SETUP INSTRUCTIONS

### Step 1: Database Setup
1. Open phpMyAdmin
2. Import `db_complete.sql`
3. This creates the `pollution_app` database with all tables

### Step 2: Create Admin Account
1. Place all files in your project folder (e.g., `htdocs/airwatch/`)
2. Open `http://localhost/airwatch/create_admin.php` in your browser
3. This creates the admin account: `admin@pollutionapp.com` / `admin123`
4. **DELETE `create_admin.php` after running it**

### Step 3: Create uploads folder
```bash
mkdir uploads
chmod 755 uploads
```

### Step 4: Test Login
- Admin: `admin@pollutionapp.com` / `admin123`
- User: Register a new account via `registration.php`

